# Lab 01: Configure Cisco Routers for Syslog, NTP, and SSH Operations

## ðŸŽ¯ Objective
   Task 1- Configure OSPF MD5 authentication.
â€¢  Task 2- Configure NTP.
â€¢  Task 3- Configure routers to log messages to the syslog server.
â€¢  Task 4- Configure R3 to support SSH connections.

## ðŸ›  Steps Taken (Task 1)
1. set up the topology

2. Configured devices in accordance with presented addressing table
- to give the routers multiple ports for serial cable connectivity. I turned off the routers and added an HWIC-2T cover and switched them back on 

3. Configure OSPF MD5 authentication and MD5 key for all the routers in area 0.
.Router 1
-conf t
router ospf 1
 router-id 1.1.1.1
 network 192.168.1.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
 network 10.1.1.0 0.0.0.3 area 0
exit

! Enable MD5 Authentication on the serial link
interface s0/1/0
 ip ospf authentication message-digest
 ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 cisco123
exit

.Router 2
conf t
router ospf 1
 router-id 2.2.2.2
 network 10.1.1.0 0.0.0.3 area 0
 network 10.2.2.0 0.0.0.3 area 0
exit

interface s0/1/0
 ip ospf authentication message-digest
 ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 cisco123
exit

interface s0/1/1
 ip ospf authentication message-digest
 ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 cisco123
exit

.Router 3
conf t
router ospf 1
 router-id 3.3.3.3
 network 192.168.3.0 0.0.0.255 area 0
 network 10.2.2.0 0.0.0.3 area 0
exit

interface s0/1/1
 ip ospf authentication message-digest
 ip ospf message-digest-key 1 md5 cisco123
exit

4.Very OSPF route is working 
-show ip ospf neighbor (on each router)

5. Ping PC-C (192.168.3.5) to NTP Server
-ping 192.168.1.5

## ðŸ“¸ Screenshots

## ðŸ›  Steps Taken (Task 2)
1. Configure NTP Server
. On the NTP server click NTP under services and enable NTP
. Set key to 1 and Password to cisco123 as previously stated 
. Set Date and Time to current Date and time 

2. Configure R1, R2, and R3 as NTP clients
-conf t
ntp server 192.168.1.5
exit
(On each router)
.Verify NTP Cinfiguration 
-show ntp associations

3. Configure routers to update hardware clock
-ntp update-calendar (On each router)
.Verify clock configuration
-show clock

4. Configure NTP authentication on R1, R2, and R3 using key 1 and password Cisco123
-R1(config)# ntp authenticate
R1(config)# ntp trusted-key 1
R1(config)# ntp authentication-key 1 md5 cisco123

-R2(config)# ntp authenticate
R2(config)# ntp trusted-key 1
R2(config)# ntp authentication-key 1 md5 cisco123

-R3(config)# ntp authenticate
R3(config)# ntp trusted-key 1
R3(config)# ntp authentication-key 1 md5 cisco123

5. Configure routers to timestamp log messages
-R1(config)# service timestamps log datetime msec
-R2(config)# service timestamps log datetime msec
-R3(config)# service timestamps log datetime msec

